# Explicit untracked items. Anything not matched by a pattern
# below is tracked. (The previous .gitignore used a catch-all
# `**` to deny by default and `!` patterns to re-include, but
# git's gitignore has a quirk: "It is not possible to re-include
# a file if a parent directory of that file is excluded." With
# `**` in effect, `htdocs/assets/js/` was excluded and the
# `!htdocs/assets/js/` re-include was silently ignored, so
# assets/js/*.js never made it into the repo. This file uses
# explicit allow-by-default with targeted deny rules for the
# handful of things we deliberately keep untracked.)

# Local secrets / config
.env
*.local

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.bak

# Docker build artifacts and the docker image tarball
htdocs/assets/netping_latest.tar.gz

# The wanportal logo (intentionally untracked; lives next to the
# kinetic.* assets that ARE tracked)
htdocs/assets/logo.png

# Test / scratch data with nested repos
tmp/

# Note: .htaccess and .user.ini were previously gitignored but are
# now tracked — they contain security configuration (CSP headers,
# session hardening) that should be version-controlled. No secrets
# live in these files.
